The hotel interior itself is a bit outdated, but the room we stayed in (in the tower) was very pleasant, relaxing and modern.	Unfortunately, there was nothing memorable about the hotel itself; it was a huge place, reminiscent of a rambling casino hotel (but without the lights or the casino), but just bland.	Even though the hotel was close to the airport, you couldn't haer the planes taking off, it was quiet and very relaxing.	If something might goes awry, the staff are quick to correct and aim to provide a memorable stay that makes you want to return.